<topic id="dita-map-edit-advanced">
  <title>The Advanced Tab</title>
  <!--Proofed-->
  <body> 
    <p>The <uicontrol>Advanced</uicontrol> tab allows you to specify advanced options for the
      transformation scenario.</p>
    <fig product="author developer editor">
      <title>Advanced Settings Tab</title>
      <image href="../img/sa_advanced_tab_dita_scenario.png"/>
    </fig>
    <fig product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">
      <title>Advanced Settings Tab</title>
      <image href="../img/ec_advanced_tab_dita_scenario.png"/>
    </fig>
    <p>You can specify the following parameters:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><uicontrol>Custom build file</uicontrol> - If you use a custom DITA-OT build file, you can
        specify the path to the customized build file. If empty, the <filepath>build.xml</filepath>
        file from the <varname>dita.dir</varname> parameter that is configured in the
          <uicontrol>Parameters</uicontrol> tab is used. An <xref
          href="editor-variables.dita#editor-variables" format="dita">editor variable</xref> can be
        inserted for the file path by using the <uicontrol><image
            href="../img/InsertEditorVariables16.png" id="image_etx_rxm_wr"/>Insert Editor
          Variables</uicontrol> button.</li>
      <li><uicontrol>Build target</uicontrol> - Optionally, you can specify a build target for the
        build file. If no target is specified, the default <codeph>init</codeph> target is
        used.</li>
      <li conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/li-additional-arguments"/>
      <li conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/li-ant-home"/>
      <li conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/li-java-home"/>
      <li conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/dita-jvm-args" id="jvm-arguments"/>
      <li conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/li-libraries"/>
    </ul>
  </body>
